    <h1>How to Convert Bank Statement PDF Tables to Excel</h1>
    <p>Bank statements are a high-value use case for PDF table extraction, but accuracy matters. Treat every exported spreadsheet as a draft until reconciled.</p>
    <h2>Use text-based statements when possible</h2>
    <p>Downloaded bank PDFs often contain selectable text, while photographed or scanned statements usually require OCR.</p>
    <h2>Check important fields</h2>
    <p>Review dates, descriptions, debits, credits, balances, and negative signs. Multi-line descriptions can shift columns in some PDFs.</p>
    <h2>Privacy matters</h2>
    <p>Use tools with clear retention policies. This tool processes files temporarily and does not create saved conversion history.</p>
